item.title: Lofi Hiphop Contest (RESULTS ANNOUNCED)
item.dc:creator: foryou
item.description:
Well, the results are in! All of you did amazing entries, so it was really hard to judge. You all have a very good idea of what lofi hiphop sounds like and you were able to incorporate it into your entries.

Now let‚Äôs move onto the honorable mentions. (These are in no particular order.)

Honorable Mention #1: @obexg

Your track was really nice. I liked the melodies that you used. A thing that I think you could‚Äôve improved on was sound choice. You had an 808-style bass (Punch) as your main bass. Although that‚Äôs a nice idea and you used it creatively, it doesn‚Äôt really fit the lofi vibe as much as a sub bass like Lake would‚Äôve. I felt like it sounded more like a trap song and brought the focus of the track away from the lofi vibe. Still, very nice track. Good job!

Honorable Mention #2: @WubDalrus

It was nice to see a new person in this community entering a contest. It‚Äôs a good way to get engaged in the Auxy Community. Your track had a strong emphasis on melodies. I liked the melodies you used, but I feel like parts of them could‚Äôve been executed better. This is partly because of your sound choice. I noticed you used a lot of sounds that emulated live instruments, like strings and a saxophone. I feel like automating the sounds a little bit more and messing with the placement of notes in your melodies (maybe making a few notes offbeat slightly on purpose to add a more human, realistic sound to it) would‚Äôve helped your track be better. Still, again, nice work! Your song was really good, and I could tell that you‚Äôre skilled at making melodies. Good job!

Now on to the first and second place prizes.

Second Place: @paroxyzm

This was very hard to judge. Both you and Yaad made really good tracks. I liked yours because of the sound choices and the melodies you used. With that being said, I feel like your entry could‚Äôve been better if you added more elements in the beginning. It felt kind of empty honestly. I feel like if you would‚Äôve added the sub bass in the beginning instead of halfway into the first part, it would‚Äôve flowed a lot better. Other than that, I think it‚Äôs a very good song, and I think you should consider making more lofi, because you definitely have the skill to do it.

And now, the moment you‚Äôve all been waiting for‚Ä¶ The winner of the Lofi Hiphop Contest is‚Ä¶

Yaad!!!

@Yaad, your entry was amazing, and I really liked what you did with the drums spoiler. I loved the vibe you created with the vinyl crackle and background ambience, and I really liked the guitar you used. Not very many Auxy producers use the guitar sounds anymore, so it was a nice change of pace from the usual Silk and Hour combo.

You will get your song reposted on my main SoundCloud account, http://www.soundcloud.com/seikatsuuu (450 followers) and you will also get your song added to many promotion networks.

Thank you all for entering! We hope to see you all in the next Lofi Hiphop Contest! Have a great rest of your year!
